FBIS4-40187 "drsov115_b_94009" FBIS-SOV-94-115 Daily Report 15 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military, Nuclear & Space Issues Yeltsin: Army To Be Reduced to 1.5 Million Yeltsin: Army To Be Reduced to 1.5 Million LD1506031794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0220 GMT 15 Jun 94 LD1506031794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service Russian BFN [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Tamara Zamyatina and Vladimir Konoplitskiy] [Text] Blagoveshchensk, 15 Jun -- At a meeting with Amur Oblast officials today, Russian President Boris Yeltsin spoke about the strategic purpose of reducing the strength of the Russian Army from three million servicemen to one and a half million. Speaking about the provision of the Russian Army with technical equipment, the president said it did not need much equipment, but it needed mobile weapons which could compete on international market. Boris Yeltsin spoke about an intention to share the arms markets for selling Russian military equipment and said that following the Malaysian example, Thailand and Australia would also be buying Russian weapons. "There are no ideological obstacles to this," Boris Yeltsin stressed.
